tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, suggesting impaired glucose tolerance or early diabetes, and a slightly increased creatinine, which may indicate reduced renal function. Mild anemia is present (low erythrocytes and hemoglobin), and total CO₂ is slightly low, possibly reflecting mild metabolic acidosis. Platelet distribution width is elevated, which may indicate increased platelet size variability. Further clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended.
